There are several fun games you can play over text with your best friend. Here are a few ideas:

Would You Rather: In this game, you take turns asking each other a "Would you rather" question, where you have to choose between two options. For example, "Would you rather be able to fly or be able to turn invisible?"

20 Questions: One person thinks of a person, place, or thing, and the other person has to ask yes or no questions to try to figure out what it is in 20 questions or less.

Trivia: You can play trivia games with each other by asking questions on various topics and keeping score of who gets the most answers correct.

Word Games: You can play games like Scrabble, Word Jumble, or Hangman over text by sending each other the letters and keeping track of the score.

Storytelling: One person starts a story with a sentence or two and sends it to the other person, who adds their own sentence or two to continue the story. Keep going back and forth until you've created a full story.

Crispy chicken and potato sticks 🍟 Ingredients 4 large potatoes ( peeled and cut into cubes ) 1/3 cup freshly grated parmesan cheese 1/2 cup shredded boiled chicken 2 tbsp corn flour 3 tbsp all purpose flour Salt to taste 1 tsp black pepper 1/2 tbsp garlic powder 1 tbsp cajun seasoning Oil for frying Method: Peel, cut and boil the potatoes. Mash the potatoes until silky and smooth , add finely chopped chicken and grated parmesan cheese. Add corn flour,ap flour,salt black pepper garlic powder and cajun seasoning. Mix well and place the mixture in a zip lock bag. Flatten the mixture with a rolling pin until evenly distributed. Freeze the mixture for 30-40 minutes until set. Take out the mixture and cut it into fries shape. Fry the potatoes on medium to high heat until crispy and golden brown. Garnish with more parmesan cheese. Serve with your favorite dipping sauce and enjoy ! #frenchfries #chickenfries #potatoes #ramadanrecipes #recipes
